#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="dn32"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "dn32:0.1"
msgid "Dīgha Nikāya 32 "
msgstr "Long Discourses 32 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "dn32:0.2"
msgid "Āṭānāṭiyasutta "
msgstr "The Āṭānāṭiya Protection "

# NOTE: i believe this is only place in whole canon that lists the bhanavara at the start.
#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "dn32:0.3"
msgid "1. Paṭhamabhāṇavāra "
msgstr "1. The First Recitation Section "

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts-cs1, pts-vp-pli3.194, sc1
msgctxt "dn32:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "dn32:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain. "

#. VAR: gijjhakūṭaṃ pabbataṃ obhāsetvā → gijjhakūṭaṃ obhāsetvā (bj, s1-3, pts1)
#. VAR: mahārājā → mahārājāno (mr)
msgctxt "dn32:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho cattāro mahārājā mahatiyā ca yakkhasenāya mahatiyā ca gandhabbasenāya mahatiyā ca kumbhaṇḍasenāya mahatiyā ca nāgasenāya catuddisaṃ rakkhaṃ ṭhapetvā catuddisaṃ gumbaṃ ṭhapetvā catuddisaṃ ovaraṇaṃ ṭhapetvā abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṃ gijjhakūṭaṃ pabbataṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. "
msgstr "Then, late at night, the Four Great Kings—with large armies of spirits, fairies, goblins, and dragons—set guards, troops, and wards at the four quarters and then, lighting up the entire Vulture’s Peak with their beauty, went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. "

msgctxt "dn32:1.4"
msgid "Tepi kho yakkhā appekacce bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu, appekacce bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu, sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu, appekacce yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu, appekacce nāmagottaṃ sāvetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu, appekacce tuṇhībhūtā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. "
msgstr "Before sitting down to one side, some spirits bowed, some exchanged greetings and polite conversation, some held up their joined palms toward the Buddha, some announced their name and clan, while some kept silent. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2, pts-vp-pli3.195, sc2
msgctxt "dn32:2.1"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho vessavaṇo mahārājā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Seated to one side, the Great King Vessavaṇa said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "dn32:2.2"
msgid "“santi hi, bhante, uḷārā yakkhā bhagavato appasannā. "
msgstr "“Sir, some high spirits have confidence in the Buddha, "

msgctxt "dn32:2.3"
msgid "Santi hi, bhante, uḷārā yakkhā bhagavato pasannā. "
msgstr "some do not. "

msgctxt "dn32:2.4"
msgid "Santi hi, bhante, majjhimā yakkhā bhagavato appasannā. "
msgstr "Some middling spirits have confidence in the Buddha, "

msgctxt "dn32:2.5"
msgid "Santi hi, bhante, majjhimā yakkhā bhagavato pasannā. "
msgstr "some do not. "

msgctxt "dn32:2.6"
msgid "Santi hi, bhante, nīcā yakkhā bhagavato appasannā. "
msgstr "Some low spirits have confidence in the Buddha, "

msgctxt "dn32:2.7"
msgid "Santi hi, bhante, nīcā yakkhā bhagavato pasannā. "
msgstr "some do not. "

msgctxt "dn32:2.8"
msgid "Yebhuyyena kho pana, bhante, yakkhā appasannāyeva bhagavato. "
msgstr "But mostly the spirits don’t have confidence in the Buddha. "

msgctxt "dn32:2.9"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn32:2.10"
msgid "Bhagavā hi, bhante, pāṇātipātā veramaṇiyā dhammaṃ deseti, adinnādānā veramaṇiyā dhammaṃ deseti, kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇiyā dhammaṃ deseti, musāvādā veramaṇiyā dhammaṃ deseti, surāmerayamajjappamādaṭṭhānā veramaṇiyā dhammaṃ deseti. "
msgstr "Because the Buddha teaches them to refrain from killing living creatures, stealing, lying, sexual misconduct, and drinking alcohol. "

msgctxt "dn32:2.11"
msgid "Yebhuyyena kho pana, bhante, yakkhā appaṭiviratāyeva pāṇātipātā, appaṭiviratā adinnādānā, appaṭiviratā kāmesumicchācārā, appaṭiviratā musāvādā, appaṭiviratā surāmerayamajjappamādaṭṭhānā. "
msgstr "But mostly they don’t refrain from such things. "

msgctxt "dn32:2.12"
msgid "Tesaṃ taṃ hoti appiyaṃ amanāpaṃ. "
msgstr "They don’t like that or approve of it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn32:2.13"
msgid "Santi hi, bhante, bhagavato sāvakā araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevanti appasaddāni appanigghosāni vijanavātāni manussarāhasseyyakāni paṭisallānasāruppāni. "
msgstr "Sir, there are disciples of the Buddha who frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest that are quiet and still, far from the madding crowd, remote from human settlements, and fit for retreat. "

msgctxt "dn32:2.14"
msgid "Tattha santi uḷārā yakkhā nivāsino, ye imasmiṃ bhagavato pāvacane appasannā. "
msgstr "There dwell high spirits who have no confidence in the Buddha’s dispensation. "

msgctxt "dn32:2.15"
msgid "Tesaṃ pasādāya uggaṇhātu, bhante, bhagavā āṭānāṭiyaṃ rakkhaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ upāsakānaṃ upāsikānaṃ guttiyā rakkhāya avihiṃsāya phāsuvihārāyā”ti. "
msgstr "To give them confidence, may the Buddha please learn the Āṭānāṭiya protection for the guarding, protection, safety, and comfort of the monks, nuns, laymen, and laywomen.” "

msgctxt "dn32:2.16"
msgid "Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena. "
msgstr "The Buddha consented in silence. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3, sc3
msgctxt "dn32:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho vessavaṇo mahārājā bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imaṃ āṭānāṭiyaṃ rakkhaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "Then, knowing that the Buddha had consented, on that occasion Great King Vessavaṇa recited the Āṭānāṭiya protection. "

# NOTE: These verses lean heavily on the translation by Anandajoti, http://www.ancient-buddhist-texts.net/Texts-and-Translations/Safeguard/03-Tatiyakabhanavaram.htm
#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc4
#. VAR: ca → cakāro bj, s1-3, pts1 potthakesu
msgctxt "dn32:3.2"
msgid "“Vipassissa ca namatthu, "
msgstr "“Hail Vipassī, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:3.3"
msgid "cakkhumantassa sirīmato; "
msgstr "the glorious seer! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:3.4"
msgid "Sikhissapi ca namatthu, "
msgstr "Hail Sikhī, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:3.5"
msgid "sabbabhūtānukampino. "
msgstr "compassionate for all beings! "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.196, sc5
#. VAR: ca → cakāro bj, s1-3, pts1 potthakesu
msgctxt "dn32:3.6"
msgid "Vessabhussa ca namatthu, "
msgstr "Hail Vesabhū, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:3.7"
msgid "nhātakassa tapassino; "
msgstr "cleansed and austere! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:3.8"
msgid "Namatthu kakusandhassa, "
msgstr "Hail Kakusandha, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:3.9"
msgid "mārasenāpamaddino. "
msgstr "crusher of Māra’s army! "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "dn32:3.10"
msgid "Koṇāgamanassa namatthu, "
msgstr "Hail Koṇāgamana, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:3.11"
msgid "brāhmaṇassa vusīmato; "
msgstr "the accomplished brahmin! "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: ca → cakāro bj, s1-3, pts1 potthakesu
msgctxt "dn32:3.12"
msgid "Kassapassa ca namatthu, "
msgstr "Hail Kassapa, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:3.13"
msgid "vippamuttassa sabbadhi. "
msgstr "freed in every way! "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "dn32:3.14"
msgid "Aṅgīrasassa namatthu, "
msgstr "Hail Aṅgīrasa, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:3.15"
msgid "sakyaputtassa sirīmato; "
msgstr "the glorious Sakyan! "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: dhammaṃ desesi → dhammamadesesi (bj, s1-3, pts1) | dhammaṃ deseti (?)
msgctxt "dn32:3.16"
msgid "Yo imaṃ dhammaṃ desesi, "
msgstr "He taught this Dhamma "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:3.17"
msgid "sabbadukkhāpanūdanaṃ. "
msgstr "that dispels all suffering. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "dn32:3.18"
msgid "Ye cāpi nibbutā loke, "
msgstr "Those in the world who are extinguished, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:3.19"
msgid "yathābhūtaṃ vipassisuṃ; "
msgstr "truly discerning, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: apisuṇātha → apisuṇā (bj, s1-3) | apisunā (pts1)
msgctxt "dn32:3.20"
msgid "Te janā apisuṇātha, "
msgstr "not backbiters; such people "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:3.21"
msgid "mahantā vītasāradā. "
msgstr "being great of heart and rid of naivety, "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "dn32:3.22"
msgid "Hitaṃ devamanussānaṃ, "
msgstr "revere that Gotama; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:3.23"
msgid "yaṃ namassanti gotamaṃ; "
msgstr "he who is helpful to gods and humans, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:3.24"
msgid "Vijjācaraṇasampannaṃ, "
msgstr "accomplished in knowledge and conduct, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:3.25"
msgid "mahantaṃ vītasāradaṃ. "
msgstr "great of heart and rid of naivety. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs4, sc10
#. VAR: sūriyo → suriyo (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn32:4.1"
msgid "Yato uggacchati sūriyo, "
msgstr "Where rises the sun—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.2"
msgid "ādicco maṇḍalī mahā; "
msgstr "Aditi’s child, the great circle, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.3"
msgid "Yassa cuggacchamānassa, "
msgstr "who in his rising "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.4"
msgid "saṃvarīpi nirujjhati; "
msgstr "dispels the night, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.5"
msgid "Yassa cuggate sūriye, "
msgstr "and of whom, when sun has risen, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.6"
msgid "‘divaso’ti pavuccati. "
msgstr "it’s said to be the day—"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "dn32:4.7"
msgid "Rahadopi tattha gambhīro, "
msgstr "there is a deep lake "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.8"
msgid "samuddo saritodako; "
msgstr "an ocean, where water flows. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.9"
msgid "Evaṃ taṃ tattha jānanti, "
msgstr "So they know that in that place "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.10"
msgid "‘samuddo saritodako’. "
msgstr "there is an ocean where waters flow. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.197, sc12
msgctxt "dn32:4.11"
msgid "Ito ‘sā purimā disā’, "
msgstr "From here that is the eastern quarter, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.12"
msgid "iti naṃ ācikkhatī jano; "
msgstr "so the people say. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.13"
msgid "Yaṃ disaṃ abhipāleti, "
msgstr "That quarter is warded "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.14"
msgid "mahārājā yasassi so. "
msgstr "by a great king, glorious, "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
#. VAR: adhipati → ādhipati (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn32:4.15"
msgid "Gandhabbānaṃ adhipati, "
msgstr "the lord of the fairies; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.16"
msgid "dhataraṭṭho’ti nāmaso; "
msgstr "his name is Dhataraṭṭha. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.17"
msgid "Ramatī naccagītehi, "
msgstr "He delights in song and dance, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.18"
msgid "gandhabbehi purakkhato. "
msgstr "honored by the fairies. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "dn32:4.19"
msgid "Puttāpi tassa bahavo, "
msgstr "And he has many mighty sons "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.20"
msgid "ekanāmāti me sutaṃ; "
msgstr "all of one name, so I’ve heard. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.21"
msgid "Asīti dasa eko ca, "
msgstr "Eighty, and ten, and one—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.22"
msgid "indanāmā mahabbalā. "
msgstr "all of them named Inda. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "dn32:4.23"
msgid "Te cāpi buddhaṃ disvāna, "
msgstr "After seeing the Awakened One, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.24"
msgid "buddhaṃ ādiccabandhunaṃ; "
msgstr "the Buddha, Kinsman of the Sun, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.25"
msgid "Dūratova namassanti, "
msgstr "they revere him from afar, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.26"
msgid "mahantaṃ vītasāradaṃ. "
msgstr "the one great of heart and rid of naivety. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "dn32:4.27"
msgid "Namo te purisājañña, "
msgstr "Homage to you, O thoroughbred! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.28"
msgid "namo te purisuttama; "
msgstr "Homage to you, supreme among men! "

# NOTE: Comm: Kusalena samekkhasīti anavajjena nipuṇena vā sabbaññutaññāṇena mahājanaṃ olokesi. I think this line is harking back to the problem the yakkhas have; they think the Buddha is judging and condemning them. By “kusala” here i understand that he sees them both “clearly”, as in he recognizes their misdeeds, and “kindly” in the sense that rather than condemning them he shows them skillfull and kindly how to be better.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.29"
msgid "Kusalena samekkhasi, "
msgstr "You’ve seen us with clarity and kindness. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.30"
msgid "amanussāpi taṃ vandanti; "
msgstr "The non-humans bow to you. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.31"
msgid "Sutaṃ netaṃ abhiṇhaso, "
msgstr "We’ve been asked many a time, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.32"
msgid "tasmā evaṃ vademase. "
msgstr "‘Do you bow to Gotama the victor?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "dn32:4.33"
msgid "‘Jinaṃ vandatha gotamaṃ’, "
msgstr "And so we ought to declare: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.34"
msgid "‘jinaṃ vandāma gotamaṃ; "
msgstr "‘We bow to Gotama the victor, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.35"
msgid "Vijjācaraṇasampannaṃ, "
msgstr "accomplished in knowledge and conduct! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:4.36"
msgid "buddhaṃ vandāma gotamaṃ’. "
msgstr "We bow to Gotama the awakened!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs5, sc18
msgctxt "dn32:5.1"
msgid "Yena petā pavuccanti, "
msgstr "It’s where the departed go, they say, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:5.2"
msgid "pisuṇā piṭṭhimaṃsikā; "
msgstr "who are dividers and backbiters, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: luddā → luddhā (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "dn32:5.3"
msgid "Pāṇātipātino luddā, "
msgstr "killers and hunters, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:5.4"
msgid "corā nekatikā janā. "
msgstr "bandits and frauds. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.198, sc19
msgctxt "dn32:5.5"
msgid "Ito ‘sā dakkhiṇā disā’, "
msgstr "From here that is the southern quarter, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:5.6"
msgid "iti naṃ ācikkhatī jano; "
msgstr "so the people say. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:5.7"
msgid "Yaṃ disaṃ abhipāleti, "
msgstr "That quarter is warded "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:5.8"
msgid "mahārājā yasassi so. "
msgstr "by a great king, glorious, "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20
msgctxt "dn32:5.9"
msgid "Kumbhaṇḍānaṃ adhipati, "
msgstr "the lord of the goblins; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:5.10"
msgid "‘virūḷho’ iti nāmaso; "
msgstr "his name is Virūḷha. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:5.11"
msgid "Ramatī naccagītehi, "
msgstr "He delights in song and dance, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:5.12"
msgid "kumbhaṇḍehi purakkhato. "
msgstr "honored by the goblins. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21
msgctxt "dn32:5.13"
msgid "Puttāpi tassa bahavo, "
msgstr "And he has many mighty sons "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:5.14"
msgid "ekanāmāti me sutaṃ; "
msgstr "all of one name, so I’ve heard. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:5.15"
msgid "Asīti dasa eko ca, "
msgstr "Eighty, and ten, and one—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:5.16"
msgid "indanāmā mahabbalā. "
msgstr "all of them named Inda. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc22
msgctxt "dn32:5.17"
msgid "Te cāpi buddhaṃ disvāna, "
msgstr "After seeing the Awakened One, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:5.18"
msgid "buddhaṃ ādiccabandhunaṃ; "
msgstr "the Buddha, Kinsman of the Sun, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:5.19"
msgid "Dūratova namassanti, "
msgstr "they revere him from afar, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:5.20"
msgid "mahantaṃ vītasāradaṃ. "
msgstr "the one great of heart and rid of naivety. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc23
msgctxt "dn32:5.21"
msgid "Namo te purisājañña, "
msgstr "Homage to you, O thoroughbred! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:5.22"
msgid "namo te purisuttama; "
msgstr "Homage to you, supreme among men! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:5.23"
msgid "Kusalena samekkhasi, "
msgstr "You’ve seen us with clarity and kindness. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:5.24"
msgid "amanussāpi taṃ vandanti; "
msgstr "The non-humans bow to you. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:5.25"
msgid "Sutaṃ netaṃ abhiṇhaso, "
msgstr "We’ve been asked many a time, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:5.26"
msgid "tasmā evaṃ vademase. "
msgstr "‘Do you bow to Gotama the victor?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc24
msgctxt "dn32:5.27"
msgid "‘Jinaṃ vandatha gotamaṃ’, "
msgstr "And so we ought to declare: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:5.28"
msgid "‘jinaṃ vandāma gotamaṃ; "
msgstr "‘We bow to Gotama the victor, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:5.29"
msgid "Vijjācaraṇasampannaṃ, "
msgstr "accomplished in knowledge and conduct! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:5.30"
msgid "buddhaṃ vandāma gotamaṃ’. "
msgstr "We bow to Gotama the awakened!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs6, sc25
msgctxt "dn32:6.1"
msgid "Yattha coggacchati sūriyo, "
msgstr "Where sets the sun—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.2"
msgid "ādicco maṇḍalī mahā; "
msgstr "Aditi’s child, the great circle, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.3"
msgid "Yassa coggacchamānassa, "
msgstr "who in his setting "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.4"
msgid "divasopi nirujjhati; "
msgstr "closes the day, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.5"
msgid "Yassa coggate sūriye, "
msgstr "and of whom, when sun has set, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.6"
msgid "‘saṃvarī’ti pavuccati. "
msgstr "it’s said to be the night—"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc26
msgctxt "dn32:6.7"
msgid "Rahadopi tattha gambhīro, "
msgstr "there is a deep lake "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.8"
msgid "samuddo saritodako; "
msgstr "an ocean, where water flows. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.9"
msgid "Evaṃ taṃ tattha jānanti, "
msgstr "So they know that in that place "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.10"
msgid "‘samuddo saritodako’. "
msgstr "there is an ocean where waters flow. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.199, sc27
msgctxt "dn32:6.11"
msgid "Ito ‘sā pacchimā disā’, "
msgstr "From here that is the western quarter, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.12"
msgid "iti naṃ ācikkhatī jano; "
msgstr "so the people say. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.13"
msgid "Yaṃ disaṃ abhipāleti, "
msgstr "That quarter is warded "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.14"
msgid "mahārājā yasassi so. "
msgstr "by a great king, glorious, "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc28
msgctxt "dn32:6.15"
msgid "Nāgānañca adhipati, "
msgstr "the lord of the dragons; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.16"
msgid "‘virūpakkho’ti nāmaso; "
msgstr "his name is Virūpakkha. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.17"
msgid "Ramatī naccagītehi, "
msgstr "He delights in song and dance, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.18"
msgid "nāgeheva purakkhato. "
msgstr "honored by the dragons. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc29
msgctxt "dn32:6.19"
msgid "Puttāpi tassa bahavo, "
msgstr "And he has many mighty sons "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.20"
msgid "ekanāmāti me sutaṃ; "
msgstr "all of one name, so I’ve heard. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.21"
msgid "Asīti dasa eko ca, "
msgstr "Eighty, and ten, and one—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.22"
msgid "indanāmā mahabbalā. "
msgstr "all of them named Inda. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc30
msgctxt "dn32:6.23"
msgid "Te cāpi buddhaṃ disvāna, "
msgstr "After seeing the Awakened One, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.24"
msgid "buddhaṃ ādiccabandhunaṃ; "
msgstr "the Buddha, Kinsman of the Sun, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.25"
msgid "Dūratova namassanti, "
msgstr "they revere him from afar, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.26"
msgid "mahantaṃ vītasāradaṃ. "
msgstr "the one great of heart and rid of naivety. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc31
msgctxt "dn32:6.27"
msgid "Namo te purisājañña, "
msgstr "Homage to you, O thoroughbred! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.28"
msgid "namo te purisuttama; "
msgstr "Homage to you, supreme among men! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.29"
msgid "Kusalena samekkhasi, "
msgstr "You’ve seen us with clarity and kindness. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.30"
msgid "amanussāpi taṃ vandanti; "
msgstr "The non-humans bow to you. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.31"
msgid "Sutaṃ netaṃ abhiṇhaso, "
msgstr "We’ve been asked many a time, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.32"
msgid "tasmā evaṃ vademase. "
msgstr "‘Do you bow to Gotama the victor?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc32
msgctxt "dn32:6.33"
msgid "‘Jinaṃ vandatha gotamaṃ’, "
msgstr "And so we ought to declare: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.34"
msgid "‘jinaṃ vandāma gotamaṃ; "
msgstr "‘We bow to Gotama the victor, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.35"
msgid "Vijjācaraṇasampannaṃ, "
msgstr "accomplished in knowledge and conduct! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:6.36"
msgid "buddhaṃ vandāma gotamaṃ’. "
msgstr "We bow to Gotama the awakened!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs7, sc33
#. VAR: uttarakuruvho → uttarakurū rammā (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn32:7.1"
msgid "Yena uttarakuruvho, "
msgstr "Where lovely Uttarakuru is, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.2"
msgid "mahāneru sudassano; "
msgstr "and the beautiful Mount Meru, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.3"
msgid "Manussā tattha jāyanti, "
msgstr "humans born there "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.4"
msgid "amamā apariggahā. "
msgstr "are unselfish, not possessive. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc34
msgctxt "dn32:7.5"
msgid "Na te bījaṃ pavapanti, "
msgstr "They do not sow the seed, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.6"
msgid "napi nīyanti naṅgalā; "
msgstr "nor do they draw the plough. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.7"
msgid "Akaṭṭhapākimaṃ sāliṃ, "
msgstr "The rice eaten by people "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.8"
msgid "paribhuñjanti mānusā. "
msgstr "ripens in untilled soil, "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.200, sc35
msgctxt "dn32:7.9"
msgid "Akaṇaṃ athusaṃ suddhaṃ, "
msgstr "free of powder or husk, pure, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.10"
msgid "sugandhaṃ taṇḍulapphalaṃ; "
msgstr "fragrant, with only the rice-grain. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.11"
msgid "Tuṇḍikīre pacitvāna, "
msgstr "They eat that food "

# NOTE: This is a literal rendering of “Tuṇḍikīre”. Comm says “Tattha kira jotikapāsāṇā nāma honti” the kira indicating their uncertainty. MW suggests a relation with tandoori; but, while that is indeed an ancient word, it seems the root is to “mud”, so unlikely here. It’s possible, though, that the commentary, familiar with some variant on tandoori, took that as the explanation. Presumably it was a pot that looked like a parrot’s beak, or perhaps which cracked the rice like a parrot. But given the context we should not discount the possibility that it was meant literally. It would hardly be the most fantastic tale told of foreign lands.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.12"
msgid "tato bhuñjanti bhojanaṃ. "
msgstr "after cooking it in a ‘parrot’s beak’. "

# NOTE: Cloven and uncloven was an important classification of animals in the dharmasastras, etc.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc36
msgctxt "dn32:7.13"
msgid "Gāviṃ ekakhuraṃ katvā, "
msgstr "Having prepared a cow with hooves uncloven, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.14"
msgid "anuyanti disodisaṃ; "
msgstr "they’re drawn about from place to place. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.15"
msgid "Pasuṃ ekakhuraṃ katvā, "
msgstr "Having prepared a beast with hooves uncloven, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.16"
msgid "anuyanti disodisaṃ. "
msgstr "they’re drawn about from place to place. "

# NOTE: I think and hope this means a rickshaw, not piggyback!
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc37
#. VAR: Itthiṃ vā vāhanaṃ → itthī-vāhanaṃ (bj, pts1) | itthiṃ vāhanaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn32:7.17"
msgid "Itthiṃ vā vāhanaṃ katvā, "
msgstr "Having prepared a woman-drawn carriage, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.18"
msgid "anuyanti disodisaṃ; "
msgstr "they’re drawn about from place to place. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.19"
msgid "Purisaṃ vāhanaṃ katvā, "
msgstr "Having prepared a man-drawn carriage, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.20"
msgid "anuyanti disodisaṃ. "
msgstr "they’re drawn about from place to place. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc38
msgctxt "dn32:7.21"
msgid "Kumāriṃ vāhanaṃ katvā, "
msgstr "Having prepared a girl-drawn carriage, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.22"
msgid "anuyanti disodisaṃ; "
msgstr "they’re drawn about from place to place. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.23"
msgid "Kumāraṃ vāhanaṃ katvā, "
msgstr "Having prepared a boy-drawn carriage, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.24"
msgid "anuyanti disodisaṃ. "
msgstr "they’re drawn about from place to place. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc39
msgctxt "dn32:7.25"
msgid "Te yāne abhiruhitvā, "
msgstr "Having ascended their vehicle, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: anupariyāyanti → anupariyanti (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn32:7.26"
msgid "Sabbā disā anupariyāyanti; "
msgstr "that king’s servants "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.27"
msgid "Pacārā tassa rājino. "
msgstr "tour about in every quarter, "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc40
msgctxt "dn32:7.28"
msgid "Hatthiyānaṃ assayānaṃ, "
msgstr "provided with vehicles, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.29"
msgid "dibbaṃ yānaṃ upaṭṭhitaṃ; "
msgstr "elephant, horse, and divine. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.30"
msgid "Pāsādā sivikā ceva, "
msgstr "And there are mansions and palanquins "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.31"
msgid "mahārājassa yasassino. "
msgstr "for that great and glorious king. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc41
msgctxt "dn32:7.32"
msgid "Tassa ca nagarā ahu, "
msgstr "And he has cities, too, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.33"
msgid "Antalikkhe sumāpitā; "
msgstr "well-built in the sky: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.34"
msgid "Āṭānāṭā kusināṭā parakusināṭā, "
msgstr "Āṭānāṭā, Kusināṭā, Parakusināṭā, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Nāṭasuriyā → nāṭapuriyā (bj, pts1) | nāṭapariyā (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn32:7.35"
msgid "Nāṭasuriyā parakusiṭanāṭā. "
msgstr "Nāṭasuriyā, and Parakusiṭanāṭā. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.201, sc42
#. VAR: kasivanto → kapivanto (bj) | kapīvanto (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn32:7.36"
msgid "Uttarena kasivanto, "
msgstr "To the north is Kapīvanta, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.37"
msgid "Janoghamaparena ca; "
msgstr "and Jonogha lies beyond. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.38"
msgid "Navanavutiyo ambaraambaravatiyo, "
msgstr "And there’s Navanavutiya, Ambara-ambaravatiya, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.39"
msgid "Āḷakamandā nāma rājadhānī. "
msgstr "and the royal capital named Āḷakamandā. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc43
msgctxt "dn32:7.40"
msgid "Kuverassa kho pana mārisa, "
msgstr "The Great King Kuvera, dear sir, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.41"
msgid "Mahārājassa visāṇā nāma rājadhānī; "
msgstr "has a capital named Visāṇā, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.42"
msgid "Tasmā kuvero mahārājā, "
msgstr "which is why the great king "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.43"
msgid "‘Vessavaṇo’ti pavuccati. "
msgstr "is called ‘Vessavaṇa’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc44
msgctxt "dn32:7.44"
msgid "Paccesanto pakāsenti, "
msgstr "These each individually inform the King: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.45"
msgid "Tatolā tattalā tatotalā; "
msgstr "Tatolā, Tattalā, Tatotalā, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.46"
msgid "Ojasi tejasi tatojasī, "
msgstr "Ojasi, Tejasi, Tatojasi, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.47"
msgid "Sūro rājā ariṭṭho nemi. "
msgstr "Sūra, Rājā, Ariṭṭha, and Nemi. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc45
msgctxt "dn32:7.48"
msgid "Rahadopi tattha dharaṇī nāma, "
msgstr "There is a lake there too named Dharaṇī, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.49"
msgid "Yato meghā pavassanti; "
msgstr "from whence the clouds rain down, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.50"
msgid "Vassā yato patāyanti, "
msgstr "and the rains disperse. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: sālavatī → bhagalavatī (bj, s1-3) | bhagalavati (pts1)
msgctxt "dn32:7.51"
msgid "Sabhāpi tattha sālavatī nāma. "
msgstr "There is a hall there too named Bhagalavatī, "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc46
msgctxt "dn32:7.52"
msgid "Yattha yakkhā payirupāsanti, "
msgstr "where the spirits frequent. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.53"
msgid "Tattha niccaphalā rukkhā; "
msgstr "There the trees are ever in fruit, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.54"
msgid "Nānā dijagaṇā yutā, "
msgstr "with many different flocks of birds. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.55"
msgid "Mayūrakoñcābhirudā; "
msgstr "Peacocks and herons call out there, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.56"
msgid "Kokilādīhi vagguhi. "
msgstr "and the sweet cuckoos too. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.202, sc47
msgctxt "dn32:7.57"
msgid "Jīvañjīvakasaddettha, "
msgstr "One bird cries out ‘Live, live!’, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.58"
msgid "atho oṭṭhavacittakā; "
msgstr "another ‘Lift up your heart!’ "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Kukkuṭakā → kukutthakā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "dn32:7.59"
msgid "Kukkuṭakā kuḷīrakā, "
msgstr "There are cocks and kookaburras, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.60"
msgid "vane pokkharasātakā. "
msgstr "and in the wood the lotus-crane. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc48
msgctxt "dn32:7.61"
msgid "Sukasāḷikasaddettha, "
msgstr "The parrots and mynah cry out there, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.62"
msgid "daṇḍamāṇavakāni ca; "
msgstr "and the ‘little stick-boy’ birds. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.63"
msgid "Sobhati sabbakālaṃ sā, "
msgstr "Kuvera’s pond of rushes "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.64"
msgid "kuveranaḷinī sadā. "
msgstr "is lovely all the time. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc49
msgctxt "dn32:7.65"
msgid "Ito ‘sā uttarā disā’, "
msgstr "From here that is the northern quarter, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.66"
msgid "iti naṃ ācikkhatī jano; "
msgstr "so the people say. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.67"
msgid "Yaṃ disaṃ abhipāleti, "
msgstr "That quarter is warded "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.68"
msgid "mahārājā yasassi so. "
msgstr "by a great king, glorious, "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc50
msgctxt "dn32:7.69"
msgid "Yakkhānañca adhipati, "
msgstr "the lord of spirits; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.70"
msgid "‘kuvero’ iti nāmaso; "
msgstr "his name is ‘Kuvera’. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.71"
msgid "Ramatī naccagītehi, "
msgstr "He delights in song and dance, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.72"
msgid "yakkheheva purakkhato. "
msgstr "honored by the spirits. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc51
msgctxt "dn32:7.73"
msgid "Puttāpi tassa bahavo, "
msgstr "And he has many mighty sons "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.74"
msgid "ekanāmāti me sutaṃ; "
msgstr "all of one name, so I’ve heard. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.75"
msgid "Asīti dasa eko ca, "
msgstr "Eighty, and ten, and one—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.76"
msgid "indanāmā mahabbalā. "
msgstr "all of them named Inda. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc52
msgctxt "dn32:7.77"
msgid "Te cāpi buddhaṃ disvāna, "
msgstr "After seeing the Awakened One, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.78"
msgid "buddhaṃ ādiccabandhunaṃ; "
msgstr "the Buddha, Kinsman of the Sun, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.79"
msgid "Dūratova namassanti, "
msgstr "they revere him from afar, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.80"
msgid "mahantaṃ vītasāradaṃ. "
msgstr "the one great of heart and rid of naivety. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc53
msgctxt "dn32:7.81"
msgid "Namo te purisājañña, "
msgstr "Homage to you, O thoroughbred! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.82"
msgid "namo te purisuttama; "
msgstr "Homage to you, supreme among men! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.83"
msgid "Kusalena samekkhasi, "
msgstr "You’ve seen us with clarity and kindness. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.84"
msgid "amanussāpi taṃ vandanti; "
msgstr "The non-humans bow to you. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.85"
msgid "Sutaṃ netaṃ abhiṇhaso, "
msgstr "We’ve been asked many a time, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.86"
msgid "tasmā evaṃ vademase. "
msgstr "‘Do you bow to Gotama the victor?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc54
msgctxt "dn32:7.87"
msgid "‘Jinaṃ vandatha gotamaṃ’, "
msgstr "And so we ought to declare: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.88"
msgid "‘jinaṃ vandāma gotamaṃ; "
msgstr "‘We bow to Gotama the victor, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.89"
msgid "Vijjācaraṇasampannaṃ, "
msgstr "accomplished in knowledge and conduct! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:7.90"
msgid "buddhaṃ vandāma gotaman’ti. "
msgstr "We bow to Gotama the awakened!’” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: pts-cs8, pts-vp-pli3.203, sc55
msgctxt "dn32:8.1"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho sā, mārisa, āṭānāṭiyā rakkhā bhikkhūnaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ upāsakānaṃ upāsikānaṃ guttiyā rakkhāya avihiṃsāya phāsuvihārāya. "
msgstr "This, dear sir, is the Āṭānāṭiya protection for the guarding, protection, safety, and comfort of the monks, nuns, laymen, and laywomen. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc56
#. VAR: pariyāputā → pariyāpuṭā (mr)
msgctxt "dn32:8.2"
msgid "Yassa kassaci, mārisa, bhikkhussa vā bhikkhuniyā vā upāsakassa vā upāsikāya vā ayaṃ āṭānāṭiyā rakkhā suggahitā bhavissati samattā pariyāputā. "
msgstr "The monks, nuns, laymen, and laywomen should learn this Āṭānāṭiya protection well and completely memorize it. "

msgctxt "dn32:8.3"
msgid "Tañce amanusso yakkho vā yakkhinī vā yakkhapotako vā yakkhapotikā vā yakkhamahāmatto vā yakkhapārisajjo vā yakkhapacāro vā, gandhabbo vā gandhabbī vā gandhabbapotako vā gandhabbapotikā vā gandhabbamahāmatto vā gandhabbapārisajjo vā gandhabbapacāro vā, kumbhaṇḍo vā kumbhaṇḍī vā kumbhaṇḍapotako vā kumbhaṇḍapotikā vā kumbhaṇḍamahāmatto vā kumbhaṇḍapārisajjo vā kumbhaṇḍapacāro vā, nāgo vā nāgī vā nāgapotako vā nāgapotikā vā nāgamahāmatto vā nāgapārisajjo vā nāgapacāro vā, paduṭṭhacitto bhikkhuṃ vā bhikkhuniṃ vā upāsakaṃ vā upāsikaṃ vā gacchantaṃ vā anugaccheyya, ṭhitaṃ vā upatiṭṭheyya, nisinnaṃ vā upanisīdeyya, nipannaṃ vā upanipajjeyya. "
msgstr "If anyone who does so is approached while walking, standing, sitting, or lying down by any non-human being with malicious intent—including males, females, boys, girls, ministers, counselors, and servants among the spirits, fairies, goblins, and dragons—"

msgctxt "dn32:8.4"
msgid "Na me so, mārisa, amanusso labheyya gāmesu vā nigamesu vā sakkāraṃ vā garukāraṃ vā. "
msgstr "that non-human will receive no homage or respect in any village or town. "

msgctxt "dn32:8.5"
msgid "Na me so, mārisa, amanusso labheyya āḷakamandāya nāma rājadhāniyā vatthuṃ vā vāsaṃ vā. "
msgstr "And they will receive no ground or dwelling in my capital of Ālakamandā. "

msgctxt "dn32:8.6"
msgid "Na me so, mārisa, amanusso labheyya yakkhānaṃ samitiṃ gantuṃ. "
msgstr "Nor will they get to go to the conference of the spirits. "

msgctxt "dn32:8.7"
msgid "Apissu naṃ, mārisa, amanussā anāvayhampi naṃ kareyyuṃ avivayhaṃ. "
msgstr "In addition, the non-humans would not give or take them in marriage. "

msgctxt "dn32:8.8"
msgid "Apissu naṃ, mārisa, amanussā attāhipi paripuṇṇāhi paribhāsāhi paribhāseyyuṃ. "
msgstr "They’d heap personal abuse on them, "

msgctxt "dn32:8.9"
msgid "Apissu naṃ, mārisa, amanussā rittampissa pattaṃ sīse nikkujjeyyuṃ. "
msgstr "drop an empty bowl on their head, "

msgctxt "dn32:8.10"
msgid "Apissu naṃ, mārisa, amanussā sattadhāpissa muddhaṃ phāleyyuṃ. "
msgstr "and even split their head into seven pieces! "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs9, pts-vp-pli3.204, sc57
#. VAR: ruddhā → ruddā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "dn32:9.1"
msgid "Santi hi, mārisa, amanussā caṇḍā ruddhā rabhasā, te neva mahārājānaṃ ādiyanti, na mahārājānaṃ purisakānaṃ ādiyanti, na mahārājānaṃ purisakānaṃ purisakānaṃ ādiyanti. "
msgstr "For there are, dear sir, non-humans who are fierce, cruel, and violent. They don’t obey the Great Kings or their men or their men’s men. "

msgctxt "dn32:9.2"
msgid "Te kho te, mārisa, amanussā mahārājānaṃ avaruddhā nāma vuccanti. "
msgstr "They’re said to be rebelling against the Great Kings. "

msgctxt "dn32:9.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, mārisa, rañño māgadhassa vijite mahācorā. "
msgstr "They’re just like the bandits in the king of Magadha’s realm "

msgctxt "dn32:9.4"
msgid "Te neva rañño māgadhassa ādiyanti, na rañño māgadhassa purisakānaṃ ādiyanti, na rañño māgadhassa purisakānaṃ purisakānaṃ ādiyanti. "
msgstr "who don’t obey the king, his men, or his men’s men, "

msgctxt "dn32:9.5"
msgid "Te kho te, mārisa, mahācorā rañño māgadhassa avaruddhā nāma vuccanti. "
msgstr "and are said to be rebelling against the king. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn32:9.6"
msgid "Evameva kho, mārisa, santi amanussā caṇḍā ruddhā rabhasā, te neva mahārājānaṃ ādiyanti, na mahārājānaṃ purisakānaṃ ādiyanti, na mahārājānaṃ purisakānaṃ purisakānaṃ ādiyanti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn32:9.7"
msgid "Te kho te, mārisa, amanussā mahārājānaṃ avaruddhā nāma vuccanti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn32:9.8"
msgid "Yo hi koci, mārisa, amanusso yakkho vā yakkhinī vā … pe … gandhabbo vā gandhabbī vā … pe … kumbhaṇḍo vā kumbhaṇḍī vā … pe … nāgo vā nāgī vā nāgapotako vā nāgapotikā vā nāgamahāmatto vā nāgapārisajjo vā nāgapacāro vā paduṭṭhacitto bhikkhuṃ vā bhikkhuniṃ vā upāsakaṃ vā upāsikaṃ vā gacchantaṃ vā anugaccheyya, ṭhitaṃ vā upatiṭṭheyya, nisinnaṃ vā upanisīdeyya, nipannaṃ vā upanipajjeyya. "
msgstr "If any non-human being with malicious intent—including males, females, boys, girls, ministers, counselors, and servants among the spirits, fairies, goblins, and dragons—approaches a monk, nun, layman, or laywoman while walking, standing, sitting, or lying down, "

msgctxt "dn32:9.9"
msgid "Imesaṃ yakkhānaṃ mahāyakkhānaṃ senāpatīnaṃ mahāsenāpatīnaṃ ujjhāpetabbaṃ vikkanditabbaṃ viravitabbaṃ: "
msgstr "one ought to yell, cry, and scream to the spirits, great spirits, generals, great generals: "

msgctxt "dn32:9.10"
msgid "‘ayaṃ yakkho gaṇhāti, ayaṃ yakkho āvisati, ayaṃ yakkho heṭheti, ayaṃ yakkho viheṭheti, ayaṃ yakkho hiṃsati, ayaṃ yakkho vihiṃsati, ayaṃ yakkho na muñcatī’ti. "
msgstr "‘This spirit’s got me! This spirit’s entered me! This spirit’s annoying me! This spirit’s harassing me! This spirit’s hurting me! This spirit’s harming me! This spirit won’t let me go!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs10, sc58
msgctxt "dn32:10.1"
msgid "Katamesaṃ yakkhānaṃ mahāyakkhānaṃ senāpatīnaṃ mahāsenāpatīnaṃ? "
msgstr "To what spirits, great spirits, generals, great generals? "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc59
msgctxt "dn32:10.2"
msgid "Indo somo varuṇo ca, "
msgstr "‘Inda, Soma, and Varuṇa, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:10.3"
msgid "bhāradvājo pajāpati; "
msgstr "Bhāradvāja, Pajāpati, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:10.4"
msgid "Candano kāmaseṭṭho ca, "
msgstr "Candana and Kāmaseṭṭha, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:10.5"
msgid "kinnughaṇḍu nighaṇḍu ca. "
msgstr "Kinnughaṇḍu and Nighaṇḍu, "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc60
msgctxt "dn32:10.6"
msgid "Panādo opamañño ca, "
msgstr "Panāda and Opamañña, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:10.7"
msgid "devasūto ca mātali; "
msgstr "and Mātali, the god’s charioteer. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:10.8"
msgid "Cittaseno ca gandhabbo, "
msgstr "Cittasena the fairy, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: janesabho → janosabho (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn32:10.9"
msgid "naḷo rājā janesabho. "
msgstr "and the kings Nala and Janesabha, "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.205, sc61
msgctxt "dn32:10.10"
msgid "Sātāgiro hemavato, "
msgstr "Sātāgira, Hemavata, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:10.11"
msgid "puṇṇako karatiyo guḷo; "
msgstr "Puṇṇaka, Karatiya, and Guḷa; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:10.12"
msgid "Sivako mucalindo ca, "
msgstr "Sivaka and Mucalinda, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:10.13"
msgid "vessāmitto yugandharo. "
msgstr "Vessāmitta, Yugandhara, "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc62
#. VAR: supparodho ca → suppagedho ca (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn32:10.14"
msgid "Gopālo supparodho ca, "
msgstr "Gopāla, Supparodha, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:10.15"
msgid "Hiri netti ca mandiyo; "
msgstr "Hiri, Netti, and Mandiya; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:10.16"
msgid "Pañcālacaṇḍo āḷavako, "
msgstr "Pañcālacaṇḍa, Āḷavaka, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Pajjunno → pajjanno (bj) | pajuṇṇo (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn32:10.17"
msgid "Pajjunno sumano sumukho; "
msgstr "Pajjunna, Sumana, Sumukha, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: maṇi māṇivaro → maṇi mānicaro (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn32:10.18"
msgid "Dadhimukho maṇi māṇivaro dīgho, "
msgstr "Dadhimukha, Maṇi, Māṇivara, Dīgha, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: serīsako → serissako (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "dn32:10.19"
msgid "Atho serīsako saha. "
msgstr "together with Serīsaka.’ "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc63
msgctxt "dn32:10.20"
msgid "Imesaṃ yakkhānaṃ mahāyakkhānaṃ senāpatīnaṃ mahāsenāpatīnaṃ ujjhāpetabbaṃ vikkanditabbaṃ viravitabbaṃ: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn32:10.21"
msgid "‘ayaṃ yakkho gaṇhāti, ayaṃ yakkho āvisati, ayaṃ yakkho heṭheti, ayaṃ yakkho viheṭheti, ayaṃ yakkho hiṃsati, ayaṃ yakkho vihiṃsati, ayaṃ yakkho na muñcatī’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs11, sc64
msgctxt "dn32:11.1"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho sā, mārisa, āṭānāṭiyā rakkhā bhikkhūnaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ upāsakānaṃ upāsikānaṃ guttiyā rakkhāya avihiṃsāya phāsuvihārāya. "
msgstr "This, dear sir, is the Āṭānāṭiya protection for the guarding, protection, safety, and comfort of the monks, nuns, laymen, and laywomen. "

msgctxt "dn32:11.2"
msgid "Handa ca dāni mayaṃ, mārisa, gacchāma bahukiccā mayaṃ bahukaraṇīyā”ti. "
msgstr "Well, now, dear sir, I must go. I have many duties, and much to do.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn32:11.3"
msgid "“Yassadāni tumhe, mahārājāno, kālaṃ maññathā”ti. "
msgstr "“Please, Great Kings, go at your convenience.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.206, sc65
msgctxt "dn32:11.4"
msgid "Atha kho cattāro mahārājā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tatthevantaradhāyiṃsu. "
msgstr "Then the Four Great Kings got up from their seats, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on their right side, before vanishing right there. "

msgctxt "dn32:11.5"
msgid "Tepi kho yakkhā uṭṭhāyāsanā appekacce bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tatthevantaradhāyiṃsu. Appekacce bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu, sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā tatthevantaradhāyiṃsu. Appekacce yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā tatthevantaradhāyiṃsu. Appekacce nāmagottaṃ sāvetvā tatthevantaradhāyiṃsu. Appekacce tuṇhībhūtā tatthevantaradhāyiṃsūti. "
msgstr "And before the other spirits present vanished, some bowed and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on their right side, some exchanged greetings and polite conversation, some held up their joined palms toward the Buddha, some announced their name and clan, while some kept silent. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn32:11.6"
msgid "Paṭhamabhāṇavāro niṭṭhito. "
msgstr "The first recitation section is finished. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn32:11.7"
msgid "2. Dutiyabhāṇavāra "
msgstr "2. The Second Recitation Section "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs12, sc66
msgctxt "dn32:12.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā tassā rattiyā accayena bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then, when the night had passed, the Buddha told the mendicants all that had happened, repeating all the verses spoken. Then he added: "

msgctxt "dn32:12.2"
msgid "“imaṃ, bhikkhave, rattiṃ cattāro mahārājā mahatiyā ca yakkhasenāya mahatiyā ca gandhabbasenāya mahatiyā ca kumbhaṇḍasenāya mahatiyā ca nāgasenāya catuddisaṃ rakkhaṃ ṭhapetvā catuddisaṃ gumbaṃ ṭhapetvā catuddisaṃ ovaraṇaṃ ṭhapetvā abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṃ gijjhakūṭaṃ pabbataṃ obhāsetvā yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn32:12.3"
msgid "Tepi kho, bhikkhave, yakkhā appekacce maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Appekacce mayā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu, sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Appekacce yenāhaṃ tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Appekacce nāmagottaṃ sāvetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Appekacce tuṇhībhūtā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc67
msgctxt "dn32:12.4"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho, bhikkhave, vessavaṇo mahārājā maṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn32:12.5"
msgid "‘santi hi, bhante, uḷārā yakkhā bhagavato appasannā … pe … santi hi, bhante, nīcā yakkhā bhagavato pasannā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn32:12.6"
msgid "Yebhuyyena kho pana, bhante, yakkhā appasannāyeva bhagavato. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn32:12.7"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn32:12.8"
msgid "Bhagavā hi, bhante, pāṇātipātā veramaṇiyā dhammaṃ deseti … surāmerayamajjappamādaṭṭhānā veramaṇiyā dhammaṃ deseti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn32:12.9"
msgid "Yebhuyyena kho pana, bhante, yakkhā appaṭiviratāyeva pāṇātipātā … appaṭiviratā surāmerayamajjappamādaṭṭhānā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn32:12.10"
msgid "Tesaṃ taṃ hoti appiyaṃ amanāpaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn32:12.11"
msgid "Santi hi, bhante, bhagavato sāvakā araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevanti appasaddāni appanigghosāni vijanavātāni manussarāhasseyyakāni paṭisallānasāruppāni. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn32:12.12"
msgid "Tattha santi uḷārā yakkhā nivāsino, ye imasmiṃ bhagavato pāvacane appasannā, tesaṃ pasādāya uggaṇhātu, bhante, bhagavā āṭānāṭiyaṃ rakkhaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ upāsakānaṃ upāsikānaṃ guttiyā rakkhāya avihiṃsāya phāsuvihārāyā’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn32:12.13"
msgid "Adhivāsesiṃ kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, tuṇhībhāvena. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn32:12.14"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vessavaṇo mahārājā me adhivāsanaṃ viditvā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imaṃ āṭānāṭiyaṃ rakkhaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc68
msgctxt "dn32:12.15"
msgid "‘Vipassissa ca namatthu, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.16"
msgid "cakkhumantassa sirīmato; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.17"
msgid "Sikhissapi ca namatthu, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.18"
msgid "sabbabhūtānukampino. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc69
msgctxt "dn32:12.19"
msgid "Vessabhussa ca namatthu, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.20"
msgid "nhātakassa tapassino; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.21"
msgid "Namatthu kakusandhassa, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.22"
msgid "mārasenāpamaddino. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc70
msgctxt "dn32:12.23"
msgid "Koṇāgamanassa namatthu, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.24"
msgid "brāhmaṇassa vusīmato; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.25"
msgid "Kassapassa ca namatthu, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.26"
msgid "vippamuttassa sabbadhi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc71
msgctxt "dn32:12.27"
msgid "Aṅgīrasassa namatthu, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.28"
msgid "sakyaputtassa sirīmato; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.29"
msgid "Yo imaṃ dhammaṃ desesi, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.30"
msgid "sabbadukkhāpanūdanaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc72
msgctxt "dn32:12.31"
msgid "Ye cāpi nibbutā loke, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.32"
msgid "yathābhūtaṃ vipassisuṃ; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.33"
msgid "Te janā apisuṇātha, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.34"
msgid "mahantā vītasāradā. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc73
msgctxt "dn32:12.35"
msgid "Hitaṃ devamanussānaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.36"
msgid "yaṃ namassanti gotamaṃ; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.37"
msgid "Vijjācaraṇasampannaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.38"
msgid "mahantaṃ vītasāradaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc74
msgctxt "dn32:12.39"
msgid "Yato uggacchati sūriyo, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.40"
msgid "ādicco maṇḍalī mahā; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.41"
msgid "Yassa cuggacchamānassa, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.42"
msgid "saṃvarīpi nirujjhati; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.43"
msgid "Yassa cuggate sūriye, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.44"
msgid "“divaso”ti pavuccati. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc75
msgctxt "dn32:12.45"
msgid "Rahadopi tattha gambhīro, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.46"
msgid "samuddo saritodako; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.47"
msgid "Evaṃ taṃ tattha jānanti, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.48"
msgid "“samuddo saritodako”. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc76
msgctxt "dn32:12.49"
msgid "Ito “sā purimā disā”, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.50"
msgid "iti naṃ ācikkhatī jano; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.51"
msgid "Yaṃ disaṃ abhipāleti, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.52"
msgid "mahārājā yasassi so. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc77
msgctxt "dn32:12.53"
msgid "Gandhabbānaṃ adhipati, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.54"
msgid "“dhataraṭṭho”ti nāmaso; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.55"
msgid "Ramatī naccagītehi, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.56"
msgid "gandhabbehi purakkhato. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc78
msgctxt "dn32:12.57"
msgid "Puttāpi tassa bahavo, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.58"
msgid "ekanāmāti me sutaṃ; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.59"
msgid "Asīti dasa eko ca, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.60"
msgid "indanāmā mahabbalā. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc79
msgctxt "dn32:12.61"
msgid "Te cāpi buddhaṃ disvāna, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.62"
msgid "buddhaṃ ādiccabandhunaṃ; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.63"
msgid "Dūratova namassanti, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.64"
msgid "mahantaṃ vītasāradaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc80
msgctxt "dn32:12.65"
msgid "Namo te purisājañña, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.66"
msgid "namo te purisuttama; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.67"
msgid "Kusalena samekkhasi, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.68"
msgid "amanussāpi taṃ vandanti; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.69"
msgid "Sutaṃ netaṃ abhiṇhaso, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.70"
msgid "tasmā evaṃ vademase. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc81
msgctxt "dn32:12.71"
msgid "“Jinaṃ vandatha gotamaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.72"
msgid "jinaṃ vandāma gotamaṃ; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.73"
msgid "Vijjācaraṇasampannaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.74"
msgid "buddhaṃ vandāma gotamaṃ”. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc82
msgctxt "dn32:12.75"
msgid "Yena petā pavuccanti, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.76"
msgid "pisuṇā piṭṭhimaṃsikā; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.77"
msgid "Pāṇātipātino luddā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn32:12.78"
